==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Delectable
<hw>De*lec"ta*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>delitable</ets>, OF. <ets>delitable</ets>, F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧lectable</ets>, fr. L. <ets>delectabilis</ets>, fr.
<ets>delectare</ets> to delight. See <er>Delight</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Highly pleasing; delightful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Delectable</qex> both to behold and taste.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>extremely pleasing to the sense of taste; same as
<er>luscious</er>, 1.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> delicious, luscious, pleasant-tasting, scrumptious,
toothsome, yummy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>De*lec"ta*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>De*lec"ta*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> -- <wf>De*lec`ta*bil"i*ty</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Delectate</ent>⟦br⟧
